## Conversation
User asked to "analyze the codebase for slowness, in particular with imports and
init. Benchmark it, include the script, and then show a flame graph of where the
hotspots are and where we can improve." Then asked to open a PR with the
benchmark results (before AND after table) and instructions for users to
reproduce before/after themselves.

## Actions
- Recreated .venv at py3.12 (uv venv --python 3.12 --clear && uv sync --group test);
  fresh Conductor workspaces ship a stale py3.14 venv where tiktoken won't build.
- Read weave/__init__.py, weave/trace/api.py, weave/trace/weave_init.py,
  weave/integrations/patch.py to map import + init paths.
- Wrote scripts/benchmarks/import_init_profile.py: subprocess timing (warmup
  discarded), -X importtime aggregation (by package + module), and a faithful
  HTML import flame graph built by reconstructing the importtime tree
  (post-order, indentation-based) — plus optional pyinstrument/py-spy.
- Installed pyinstrument (uv pip install, into venv) and tuna (uv tool install).
  py-spy was already a uv tool but needs sudo on macOS, so it's best-effort.

## Errors & Mistakes
- First attempt to capture a BEFORE flame graph used `git stash push -- $FILES`
  and `git checkout -- $FILES` with a zsh variable holding two space-separated
  paths. zsh does NOT word-split unquoted vars, so both paths were passed as a
  single pathspec: stash silently no-op'd and checkout errored. Result: a
  mislabeled "before" run that was actually the fixed code. Fixed by passing
  paths as explicit separate args ("$A" "$B").
- Dynamically loading the profiler module via importlib for an ad-hoc icicle
  print failed with AttributeError on dataclass (slots) until I registered it in
  sys.modules before exec_module.
- pyinstrument (0.1ms sampling) over-weighted call-heavy pure-Python
  (pydantic model_rebuild in query.py, lark grammar build), suggesting query.py
  was a huge cost; -X importtime (authoritative) showed it's ~12ms. Trust
  importtime for magnitude, pyinstrument for call-stack structure.

## Dead Ends
- py-spy SVG on macOS: needs root; handled gracefully (skip + message).
- Benchmarking real (enabled) init offline: not possible without auth + server;
  measured the disabled path (~0ms) and documented that real init is network RTTs.

## Hints for Future Agents
- bash grep here is ripgrep: `-E`/`--include` error out, `\|` is literal.
- .artifacts/ is gitignored; pyinstrument HTML is 10-20MB (show_all + fine
  interval) — the 60-80KB flame_importtime.html is the better shareable artifact.
- Run the profiler with the project venv's python so `import weave` resolves to
  the local checkout, not a pinned PyPI build.

## Codebase Discoveries
- weave/__init__.py eagerly imports the whole public API surface.
- `weave.init()` code cost is ~0; implicit_patch() only scans sys.modules,
  register_import_hook() is one meta_path.insert. Wall-clock is network.

